HEADWORD: Lifeblood
<hw>Life"blood`</hw> <pr>(l⟦imac⟧f"bl⟦ucr⟧d`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The blood necessary to life; vital blood.</def>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fig.: That which gives strength and
energy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Money [is] the <qex>lifeblood</qex> of the nation.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

